CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1778454187
OL,3,CRussia holds scaled down Victory Day
OL,4,Cparade amid three-day ceasefire
OL,6,FPutin, in power for more than a
OL,7,Fquarter-century, has used Victory Day,
OL,8,FRussia's most important secular
OL,9,Fholiday, to showcase the country's
OL,10,Fmilitary might and rally support for
OL,11,Fhis military action in Ukraine, now in
OL,12,Fits fifth year.
OL,14,FSpeaking at the parade, Putin hailed
OL,15,FRussian troops fighting in Ukraine,
OL,16,Fdeclaring that they "face an
OL,17,Faggressive force that is armed and
OL,18,Fsupported by the entire bloc of Nato,"
OL,19,Fand are fighting for a "just cause".
OL,26,@xD@UOU{D@XOU{D@cO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
