OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1778454187
OL,3,CRussia holds scaled down Victory Day
OL,4,Cparade amid three-day ceasefire
OL,6,FState television commentators said
OL,7,Fthat the heavy weaponry was more
OL,8,Fneeded at the battlefield in Ukraine.
OL,10,FFor the first time, Saturday's parade
OL,11,Ffeatured troops from North Korea, a
OL,12,Ftribute to Pyongyang that sent its
OL,13,Fsoldiers to fight alongside Moscow
OL,14,Fforces to repel a Ukrainian incursion
OL,15,Finto Russia's Kursk region.
OL,17,FRussia declared a unilateral ceasefire
OL,18,Ffor Friday and Saturday, while
OL,19,FUkrainian President Volodymyr
OL,20,FZelenskyy announced a truce that was
OL,21,Fsupposed to begin on May 6.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
